b'' b'h01sav.dsyibm.desy.de (michael m. savitski) writes:' b' hi, there!' b" i have a mac lc and consider buying cd300. i've been told," b' however, that:' b' the double speed of cd300 is achievable only on machines' b' with scsi-2.' b'' b"wrong, the cd300 (external) is just a plain ol' scsi device." b'' b' the double speed is a prerequisite for photocd multisession' b' capability, which i need.' b'' b'no, multisession capability and double speed are two different thing. its just' b'that the newer cd rom drives have both capability. multisession means that' b'when you put more pictures on a photo cd after the first session, the drive can' b'read and display them. double speeds just transfer any type of data (excluding' b'sound) at around double the speed.' b'' b' which means i seem to gain nothing compared with, say cd150.' b'' b'cd150 is not multisession capable. this means that you lose the ability to add' b'any more pictures after the first time (must buy a new cd). finally, since the' b'cd150 is not a double speed drive, it will require twice as long to transfer' b'data (excluding sound).' b'' b' michael m. savitski tel: b' desy-deutsches elektronen synchrotron fax: b' notkestr. d2000 hamburg germany b' decnet vxdesy::savitski' b' 